OmniScripts Disclosure Element

Enable users to agree to a disclosure statement by adding a Disclosure element to your OmniScript. Enter the copy in a rich text editor.

Drag a Disclosure element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
(Optional) Select the Required field to make selecting the checkbox next to the statement required.
(Optional) Click the Text field to enter the text for your disclosure statement.
(Optional) For additional properties, see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions.

Disclosure Properties

With the Disclosure element, enable users to read a disclosure statement and select a checkbox to indicate agreement.
title: OmniScript Disclosure Element
